public class epp_Exception
extends org.omg.CORBA.UserException
implements org.omg.CORBA.portable.IDLEntity

Class that acts as a container for any exception thrown if a communication error occurs with the EPP server or if the EPP server returns an error code.

An EPP response code is considered an error code if the numeric value is greater than or equal to 2000. Communication errors are not official EPP errors but the sake of consistency, they have been defined in the RTK with values in the 2600-2699 range. The error codes and symbolic names for these are defined in epp_Action. $Header: /cvsroot/epp-rtk/epp-rtk/java/src/org/openrtk/idl/epp0604/epp_Exception.java,v 1.1 2003/03/21 15:53:57 tubadanm Exp $
